path.xlink:title: 15 May 2014 Finance Minister Bill English delivers the 2014 budget. Surplus for 2014/15 year is $372m. Key initiatives include extending free GP visits to children 12 and under (currently 5 and under), increasing paid maternity leave from 14 weeks to 18 weeks, and increasing Working for Families parental tax credit from $150 to $220 per week. Opposition parties suggest the surplus was produced by "fudging" the numbers and reducing funding for the Christchurch rebuild.

Key initiatives include extending free GP visits to children 12 and under (currently 5 and under), increasing paid maternity leave from 14 weeks to 18 weeks, and increasing Working for Families parental tax credit from $150 to $220 per week. Opposition parties suggest the surplus was produced by "fudging" the numbers and reducing funding for the Christchurch rebuild.
